Frequently asked
questions

Why Enneagram?

There are plenty of systems that exist to help us understand and get along with one another. Enneagram is unique because it is the only system that types on motivation, rather than behavior. There are billions of iterations of behavior that can generally be traced to 9 motivations or ways of seeing. Rather than the more static, check the box systems that label individuals based on actions, Enneagram application recognizes that behaviors are adaptable and provides individuals with a unique tool for maximizing efforts in the workplace. Whereas other systems are informative, Enneagram is transformative.

Do you recommend an online test to find Enneagram type?

WE do not. Correctly identifying Enneagram type is crucial. Online tests have proven to be incorrect more than 50% of the time. Written indicators ask questions about behavior. As our behaviors change, so do our answers to those questions.

What is the best way to introduce Enneagram in the workplace?

Taking time to learn, in person and as a team, consistently proves to be the best way to carry forward and implement Enneagram understanding. An introductory Know Your Number (KYN) takes 3-6 hours of instruction time for a group session. If a team setting is not possible, KYN can be arrived at in 60-90 minutes with a 1:1 session, offered in person or remotely through a virtual meeting platform.

What are the next steps once individual type is known?

Once Enneagram type is known, WE offer modules designed for interactive team settings. These 7 follow-up modules are three hours in length, range from beginner to intermediate, and facilitate specific and collaborative application of Enneagram understanding among teams. Offered in person.

What do you offer as an alternative or enhancement to team sessions?

WE offer 1:1 sessions that focus on individual employee self-examen, relationships (work and/or personal), and employee management. These 60-90 minute sessions are offered in person or virtually. WE also offer smaller team sessions (2-5 employees) tailored to address unique professional dynamics, offered in person or virtually.
